keyFacts: The document is a confidential TECS Person Encounter List generated by U.S. Customs and Border Protection on April 6, 2021, containing 30 travel records.
The travel pattern shows frequent flights between Los Angeles (LAX) and London (LHR) from 2004 through 2019, primarily on Virgin Atlantic.
A notable flight on May 17, 2009, shows travel from Miami (MIA) to Nassau, Bahamas (NAS), a location associated with Jeffrey Epstein's private island.
The document uses APIS (Advanced Passenger Information System) and other airline data to track passenger status ('ON BOARD', 'PASSENGER', 'NOT ON BOARD').
The document reference numbers (SDNY_GM_02753139, etc.) indicate it is part of the Southern District of New York's Epstein case materials.
